  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cash Transfer Program in Communities Affected by Hurricanes Irma and Maria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This $50,000 Grant will enable the two Lutheran agencies to provide Unmet Needs grants to survivor households. Each household can receive up to $500 in Unmet Needs Grant. The process is managed by the disaster case managers of each organization and the approval process will follow protocol set up by each agency to ensure fairness, effectiveness and confidentiality of clients. $35,000 will be designated for Puerto Rico and the remaining $15,000 for US Virgin Islands. As $500 is the maximum amount each household will receive, this project will benefit at least 100 households.</narrative>
  </description>
